    "body": "### Problem\n\nnvim 9.5, debian 13, Sway/DWL, Foot/Kitty etc\n\n```\nset mouse=\nset mousescroll=ver:0,hor:0\n```\nmouse scrolling file by wheel\n\ntrying this:\n```\nnoremap <ScrollWheelUp> <nop>\nnoremap <ScrollWheelDown> <nop>\nnoremap <S-ScrollWheelUp> <nop>\nnoremap <S-ScrollWheelDown> <nop>\n```\nmouse still scrolling file by wheel\n\nin Vim 9 the same behavior\n\nOn Xorg session is all fine\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nrun nvim on wayland (wlroots) and try disable mouse. Wheel scrolling disabled only on Xorg session...\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ndisable mouse and use only for select/paste text (by middle button)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.95\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux Debian 12/13\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nFoot/kitty/alacritty/Urxvt (latest)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nand xterm too\n\n### Installation\n\napt ",
